{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774458130,"nonce":"+vYKs5DSUNFAh5pxuhBX1QiXr7I=","title":"Part 1 analysis: unit preferences (tuning to goal positions and forces)","message":"Umbrella: 297260c (Part 1)\n\n**Motivation:** Characterize what task variables individual network units encode. Are units tuned to goal direction? To control force direction? This connects the RNN solution to known neural tuning properties in motor cortex.\n\n**Approach:** Use the `UnitPreferences` analysis from feedbax to regress unit activity against goal positions and control forces during acceleration/deceleration epochs. Includes 3D visualization of planar regression fits showing preferred directions.\n\n**Status:** Module exists at `src/rlrmp/modules/analysis/part1/unit_prefs.py`. Analyzes preferences for both goal positions and control forces. Includes helper function `plot_planar_regression` for 3D scatter+vector visualization.\n\n**References:** Georgopoulos et al. (1982) for directional tuning; Todorov (2000) for optimal feedback control perspective on tuning.","files":null}]}